cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image inpainting, which is a computer vision problem, and specifically focuses on incorporating image semantics through generative models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces an improved version of the Wasserstein generative adversarial network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new optimization loss for inpainting, which involves incorporating contextual and perceptual content inherent in the image itself, and thus could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image processing and graphics (cs.GR - Graphics) and multimedia (cs.MM - Multimedia).
